WEBVTT

00:02.728 --> 00:07.047
♪ ♪

00:08.751 --> 00:10.342
Mmm. When I die,

00:10.494 --> 00:12.736
we should totally
get this sandwich place

00:12.829 --> 00:13.679
for my memorial.

00:13.830 --> 00:16.849
So good. Mmm. Can't wait.

00:17.076 --> 00:20.410
Oh, all these people
loved Mr. Chase.

00:20.429 --> 00:22.913
His students
are taking it so hard.

00:22.931 --> 00:25.507
Yeah, nobody grieves
like theater kids.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.526
(wailing)

00:29.179 --> 00:30.604
(Marge gasps)

00:30.698 --> 00:32.105
This is my show!

00:32.199 --> 00:35.016
Why are they singing
about computers?

00:35.110 --> 00:37.127
It was a musical about Y2K,

00:37.129 --> 00:39.521
which was very scary back then.

00:39.540 --> 00:42.041
Scarier than anything
we have now.

00:42.268 --> 00:44.376
The whole show takes place
on New Year's Eve,

00:44.528 --> 00:47.212
-1999...
-♪
<i> Five, four, three</i>
♪

00:47.364 --> 00:50.107
♪<i> Two, zero, zero, zero</i> ♪

00:50.125 --> 00:54.628
♪<i> A midnight countdown to Y2K</i> ♪

00:54.780 --> 00:59.283
♪<i> Five, four, three, two,</i>
<i> will I be a zero?</i>
♪

00:59.301 --> 01:04.063
♪<i> When tomorrow becomes today.</i> ♪

01:04.139 --> 01:05.972
Mom, which one are you?

01:06.067 --> 01:08.141
I was right over here.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.903
In the wings,
calling all the shots...

01:11.054 --> 01:14.055
as the stage manager.

01:14.075 --> 01:17.859
Mrs. Chase,
I'm so sorry for your loss.

01:17.894 --> 01:19.078
Oh, thank you, dear.

01:19.305 --> 01:21.580
Say, look what I found
when I was cleaning out

01:21.731 --> 01:23.398
-Franklin's office.
-(gasps)

01:23.417 --> 01:24.899
My prompt book.

01:24.919 --> 01:26.901
This binder lists all the cues

01:26.995 --> 01:29.254
for the entire production.

01:29.406 --> 01:32.499
Oh, Franklin always said you
were the heart of the show--

01:32.651 --> 01:36.169
that your stage managing
was so... zealous.

01:36.263 --> 01:38.580
I definitely ran a tight ship.

01:38.748 --> 01:41.249
But in a fun way
everyone loved, obviously.

01:41.268 --> 01:43.435
-Oh, yeah, totally.
-Super fun.

01:43.587 --> 01:46.271
Of course, I would have loved
to have been in the show,

01:46.498 --> 01:48.256
except I'm not much of a singer.

01:48.275 --> 01:52.277
But in my imagination, I've got
the voice of a Disney princess.

01:52.429 --> 01:53.170
Oh...

01:53.188 --> 01:55.172
What a special time.

01:55.265 --> 01:58.008
I'd give anything
to feel that magic again.

01:58.026 --> 02:00.869
♪ ♪

02:02.531 --> 02:05.624
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> Script notes and sound cues</i>
♪

02:05.775 --> 02:08.443
♪<i> Take me there again</i> ♪

02:08.520 --> 02:10.778
♪<i> In my blacks</i>
<i> in the backs of the wings</i>
♪

02:10.873 --> 02:13.132
♪<i> So I'm not seen</i> ♪

02:15.210 --> 02:17.285
♪<i> No one knows the magic</i> ♪

02:17.304 --> 02:22.182
♪<i> That hides</i>
<i> behind the scenes</i>
♪

02:23.051 --> 02:24.868
(regular voice):
It's me!

02:24.961 --> 02:27.053
The cast said yes!

02:27.206 --> 02:29.648
We're putting on a musical!

02:29.799 --> 02:31.984
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> Places, everybody</i>
♪

02:32.135 --> 02:34.394
♪<i> It's time to start the show</i> ♪

02:34.546 --> 02:36.546
♪<i> That's what actors</i>
<i> need me to say</i>
♪

02:36.640 --> 02:38.899
♪<i> Otherwise, they wouldn't</i>
<i> know where to go</i>
♪

02:38.993 --> 02:40.734
♪<i> Cinch up the hemlines</i> ♪

02:40.828 --> 02:43.220
♪<i> Sound check all the mics</i> ♪

02:43.313 --> 02:45.238
♪<i> Close the door,</i>
<i> ring the bell</i>
♪

02:45.391 --> 02:48.167
♪<i> And bring down</i>
<i> the house lights</i>
♪

02:48.394 --> 02:53.154
♪<i> It's curtains up</i>
<i> for Marge Bouvier</i>
♪

02:53.174 --> 02:56.233
♪<i> 'Cause I'm once again</i>
<i> the star</i>
♪

02:56.251 --> 02:58.084
♪<i> Of the backstage</i> ♪

02:58.237 --> 03:00.012
Wow, you're the director?

03:00.239 --> 03:03.015
(regular voice): No, more
important-- the stage manager.

03:03.166 --> 03:05.333
-Ah!
-Five minutes, guys!

03:05.427 --> 03:07.260
-Thank you, five.
-Five minutes.

03:07.354 --> 03:10.672
I always used to love
saying that, before...

03:10.691 --> 03:13.099
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> The endless loads</i>
<i> of laundry</i>

03:13.194 --> 03:15.252
♪<i> The dishes piled high</i> ♪

03:15.345 --> 03:17.270
♪<i> The whining and complaining</i> ♪

03:17.439 --> 03:18.772
-♪<i> It's mine</i> ♪
-♪
<i> It's mine</i>
♪

03:18.924 --> 03:20.848
-BOTH: ♪<i> It's mine</i> ♪
-(regular voice): Enough!

03:20.868 --> 03:26.187
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> I'm returning to my</i>
<i> theater family</i>

03:26.207 --> 03:31.210
♪<i> A revival of</i>
<i> our fondest memories</i>
♪

03:31.361 --> 03:32.786
-♪<i> Singin'...</i> ♪
-♪
<i> Do</i>
♪

03:32.938 --> 03:34.604
-♪<i> Re</i> ♪
-♪
<i> Mi</i>
♪

03:34.623 --> 03:37.549
-♪<i> This ♪</i>
<i> -♪ Show</i>
♪
-♪

03:37.776 --> 03:39.867
♪<i> The talk of the town</i> ♪

03:39.887 --> 03:43.055
♪<i> A hit, a smash, the rage</i> ♪

03:43.206 --> 03:46.116
♪<i> And there's nothing</i>
<i> Springfield needs more</i>
♪

03:46.134 --> 03:47.451
♪<i> Than a play</i> ♪

03:47.469 --> 03:48.894
(regular voice):
Good!

03:49.063 --> 03:51.638
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> 'Cause I'm once again the</i>
♪

03:51.790 --> 03:54.458
♪<i> Appreciated, well-respected,</i>
<i> never, ever disconnected</i>
♪

03:54.551 --> 03:55.976
♪<i> Nothing but</i>
<i> the most impressive</i>
♪

03:56.128 --> 03:57.461
♪<i> Everybody's dearest friended</i> ♪

03:57.554 --> 04:00.221
♪<i> Star</i> ♪

04:00.315 --> 04:03.558
♪<i> Of the backstage...</i> ♪

04:03.635 --> 04:05.485
♪<i> She's the star,</i>
<i> see how she shines</i>
♪

04:05.637 --> 04:09.155
♪<i> She answers</i>
<i> when we call for lines</i>
♪

04:09.250 --> 04:12.459
♪<i> Places, everybody!</i> ♪

04:14.738 --> 04:17.314
Wow, honey,
those dorks are so excited to be

04:17.316 --> 04:18.573
in your show again.

04:18.667 --> 04:19.574
And I will do everything

04:19.593 --> 04:21.242
I can to support you...

04:21.262 --> 04:22.819
while I'm at Moe's.

04:22.838 --> 04:24.170
Mwah.

04:24.265 --> 04:27.248
Sorry, Marge, but I got to
drop out of the show.

04:27.342 --> 04:28.916
I broke my hip
while singing and dancing

04:28.936 --> 04:30.352
about feeling young again.

04:31.438 --> 04:33.847
Say, Dad, what if
you filled in for Lenny

04:33.999 --> 04:35.515
and joined Mom's musical?

04:35.667 --> 04:39.444
Yeah, then you'd be the most
supportive husband ever.

04:39.671 --> 04:40.928
Great idea, kids.

04:41.023 --> 04:42.114
I'm all in, babe!

04:42.341 --> 04:45.033
One pair of super tight
dance pants, please!

04:45.861 --> 04:47.286
(laughing)

04:47.513 --> 04:50.180
From this day forward,
we are enemies.

04:50.198 --> 04:51.957
Forever and ever.

04:52.108 --> 04:53.792
Forever.

04:54.019 --> 04:55.294
<i> MARGE:</i>
<i> Okay,</i>

04:55.370 --> 04:59.372
back on stage-- it's just like
we're teenagers again.

04:59.466 --> 05:01.691
Now let's start the rehearsal.

05:01.860 --> 05:02.950
Theater!

05:03.045 --> 05:05.378
Wait, we can't start
without Sasha Reed.

05:05.531 --> 05:06.972
-She was the star of the show.
-Mm-hmm.

05:07.049 --> 05:08.715
She got into Julliard.

05:08.867 --> 05:09.808
(sighs)

05:09.959 --> 05:10.884
Sasha.
(chuckles)

05:11.036 --> 05:12.477
You never forget
your first diva.

05:12.629 --> 05:14.813
I'd love to know
what she's been up to.

05:14.890 --> 05:16.706
Well, as your dutiful
stage manager,

05:16.800 --> 05:20.468
I did reach out repeatedly,
but never heard back.

05:20.562 --> 05:22.896
I guess we'll never know
what happened

05:22.990 --> 05:25.640
after Sasha
left little old Springfield

05:25.659 --> 05:27.050
for New York City.

05:27.143 --> 05:28.476
WOMAN:
Never say never!

05:28.495 --> 05:30.645
Hello, old friends!

05:30.739 --> 05:32.664
Ah! It's Sasha!

05:32.816 --> 05:36.393
Let me tell you all about it.

05:36.411 --> 05:38.578
♪<i> It was a cold</i>
<i> and rainy morning</i>
♪

05:38.730 --> 05:40.672
♪<i> When I exited the bus</i> ♪

05:40.841 --> 05:43.008
♪<i> I stepped into the city</i> ♪

05:43.159 --> 05:45.677
♪<i> Everyone in such a rush</i> ♪

05:45.829 --> 05:48.071
♪<i> I suppose I started singing</i> ♪

05:48.164 --> 05:50.182
♪<i> Just to keep</i>
<i> the chill at bay</i>
♪

05:50.333 --> 05:53.076
♪<i> I guess I sounded</i>
<i> something like</i>
♪

05:53.169 --> 05:56.521
♪<i> This</i> ♪

05:56.673 --> 06:01.418
♪<i> And that's when I heard</i>
<i> a man say</i>
♪

06:01.436 --> 06:03.845
♪<i> "That tone, that pitch</i> ♪

06:03.864 --> 06:05.847
♪<i> "Your voice'll make us rich</i> ♪

06:05.941 --> 06:10.017
♪<i> Stick with me, and you'll</i>
<i> be destined to impress"</i>
♪

06:10.037 --> 06:11.761
♪<i> And that's how Sasha became</i> ♪

06:11.780 --> 06:14.522
♪<i> A massive success</i> ♪

06:14.600 --> 06:15.615
♪<i> Yes, Sasha</i> ♪

06:15.767 --> 06:18.085
♪<i> Is a massive success</i> ♪

06:19.438 --> 06:20.437
(exclaiming)

06:20.530 --> 06:23.048
♪<i> Now I dine on the veranda</i> ♪

06:23.199 --> 06:25.366
♪<i> With Lin-Manuel Miranda</i> ♪

06:25.460 --> 06:28.128
♪<i> Scrape meat off the bone</i>
<i> with Patti LuPone</i>
♪

06:28.280 --> 06:29.796
♪<i> Don't mention Glenn Close</i> ♪

06:29.948 --> 06:31.615
♪<i> I eat Bananas Foster</i> ♪

06:31.633 --> 06:33.725
♪<i> With my good friend</i>
<i> Sutton Foster</i>
♪

06:33.802 --> 06:37.062
♪<i> Thanks to Stephen Sondheim,</i>
<i> who's the most gracious host</i>
♪

06:37.213 --> 06:40.290
♪<i> Yes, I'm everything</i>
<i> you thought I'd be</i>
♪

06:40.308 --> 06:42.626
♪<i> When I left Springfield</i>
<i> for the big city</i>
♪

06:42.719 --> 06:46.029
♪<i> I've made it,</i>
<i> I'm a cut above the rest</i>
♪

06:47.056 --> 06:49.983
♪<i> 'Cause Sasha has returned</i> ♪

06:50.152 --> 06:51.576
♪<i> A massive</i> ♪

06:51.803 --> 06:55.705
♪<i> Success...</i> ♪

06:57.492 --> 06:58.642
♪<i> That's right</i> ♪

06:58.660 --> 06:59.976
♪<i> I'm a Broadway</i> ♪

07:00.069 --> 07:05.132
♪<i> Star!</i> ♪

07:07.761 --> 07:10.837
Oh, I can't believe
Sasha came back.

07:10.989 --> 07:12.338
What a career!

07:13.583 --> 07:16.101
I know a famous person
that knows what's his name,

07:16.328 --> 07:18.186
who is she,
and never heard of him!

07:18.939 --> 07:21.164
Okay, okay, everybody.

07:21.257 --> 07:24.443
It's so exciting that
Sasha is a massive success,

07:24.594 --> 07:27.187
but we really need
to walk through our blocking.

07:27.339 --> 07:28.763
Let's make it precise, gang!

07:28.782 --> 07:30.765
Blocking, so important.

07:30.784 --> 07:32.600
That's what Hal always told me.

07:32.619 --> 07:33.860
Hal Prince.

07:33.954 --> 07:35.454
Boom! Named it!

07:35.605 --> 07:38.105
But before we get into
the technical stuff,

07:38.200 --> 07:42.035
we need to reconnect
as an ensemblé.

07:42.187 --> 07:44.445
Let's all go to my lake house
and do trust falls.

07:44.614 --> 07:47.148
But we have to carve out
some time to run lines.

07:47.150 --> 07:50.802
(chuckles) Marge Bouvier,
you have not changed a bit.

07:50.954 --> 07:53.120
Okay, Mom, we'll run lines,

07:53.140 --> 07:54.714
but don't wait up for us.

07:54.866 --> 07:56.049
Us? What do you mean?

07:56.201 --> 07:58.551
This bonding session
is for the cast.

07:58.704 --> 08:00.479
You understand, right?

08:00.630 --> 08:01.554
Oh.

08:01.707 --> 08:03.815
Sure.
Of course.

08:03.967 --> 08:06.042
Come on, friends!
(laughs)

08:06.061 --> 08:09.062
I was wrong.
Theater kids are super cool.

08:09.156 --> 08:10.447
Thanks for the hookup, honey.

08:12.308 --> 08:14.034
♪ ♪

08:18.740 --> 08:21.816
♪<i> How will I stay alive?</i> ♪

08:21.910 --> 08:23.835
♪<i> When all</i> ♪

08:23.987 --> 08:26.079
♪<i> The computers think I died?</i> ♪

08:26.231 --> 08:28.748
-♪<i> How will I</i> ♪
-♪
<i> How will I</i>
♪

08:28.900 --> 08:30.750
<i> ♪ Stay alive ♪</i>

08:30.902 --> 08:34.237
♪<i> When all the clocks</i>
<i> and the computers</i>
♪

08:34.330 --> 08:37.224
♪<i> Think I died?</i> ♪

08:42.189 --> 08:45.081
Okay, the curtain-raiser
went a smidge long,

08:45.100 --> 08:46.841
so stay on your marks next time.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.693
-Take five!
-Thank you, five.

08:48.920 --> 08:52.680
Anyway, I hope you all remember
the best part of rehearsal...

08:52.699 --> 08:54.199
brownies!

08:54.350 --> 08:58.370
Are those Margie's Brownies
with walnuts and M&Ms?

08:59.264 --> 09:01.206
It's true, I do matter.

09:01.357 --> 09:03.691
Look what else I'm included in.

09:03.785 --> 09:05.359
It's all from our shows.

09:05.453 --> 09:07.862
We were such
a tight-knit group.

09:07.881 --> 09:09.939
Remember the tightness
of the knitting?

09:10.033 --> 09:12.292
(inhales)
There's my old guitar pick.

09:12.460 --> 09:16.471
Oh, I haven't played guitar
since I lost this!

09:17.949 --> 09:19.015
Still works!

09:20.302 --> 09:22.543
Oh, man, this takes me back...

09:22.637 --> 09:23.728
Remember, guys?

09:24.731 --> 09:26.639
♪<i> Bonfires at Billy's</i> ♪

09:26.733 --> 09:30.235
♪<i> We'd talk about our dreams</i> ♪

09:33.632 --> 09:35.982
♪<i> We'd get drunk</i>
<i> and make out, ha</i>
♪

09:36.134 --> 09:38.468
♪<i> Cause a scene</i> ♪

09:38.561 --> 09:40.394
Remind me who Billy was again?

09:40.488 --> 09:41.955
You know-- Billy.

09:42.899 --> 09:44.841
♪<i> Late nights at the diner</i> ♪

09:44.843 --> 09:47.752
♪<i> We'd laugh and we'd cry</i> ♪

09:47.979 --> 09:50.146
Right. Uh-huh.
The diner.

09:50.165 --> 09:53.240
♪<i> Smoking clove cigarettes</i> ♪

09:53.260 --> 09:56.410
♪<i> Ruthie serving us</i>
<i> cheese fries</i>
♪

09:56.430 --> 09:58.154
Is that why you guys
always smelled

09:58.173 --> 09:59.097
like burnt cinnamon?

09:59.266 --> 10:02.175
♪<i> Climbing the water tower</i> ♪

10:02.269 --> 10:04.269
♪<i> Drunk on whiskey sours</i> ♪

10:04.496 --> 10:07.330
♪<i> Stealing the Lard Lad sign</i> ♪

10:07.349 --> 10:09.608
-That was you guys?
-Yeah.

10:09.793 --> 10:11.517
♪<i> Remember the times</i> ♪

10:11.670 --> 10:13.445
♪<i> The best times</i> ♪

10:13.521 --> 10:15.614
♪<i> Of our lives</i> ♪

10:15.765 --> 10:19.492
♪<i> We had nothing but times</i> ♪

10:20.679 --> 10:23.363
♪<i> Remember the times</i> ♪

10:23.457 --> 10:26.366
Okay, I might've missed
some of those specific moments,

10:26.460 --> 10:29.352
but I'm sure I'll remember
all the other ones.

10:29.371 --> 10:31.087
What else?

10:32.633 --> 10:34.540
♪<i> The kegger at Marge's</i> ♪

10:34.635 --> 10:36.709
♪<i> What an epic night</i> ♪

10:36.862 --> 10:38.970
Wait, there was a party
at my house?

10:39.122 --> 10:40.621
Where was I?

10:40.699 --> 10:43.716
♪<i> She was at</i>
<i> a tech run-through</i>
♪

10:43.869 --> 10:45.810
♪<i> Nowhere in sight</i> ♪

10:45.962 --> 10:49.147
Guys, that's like,
pretty messed up.

10:50.133 --> 10:51.391
♪<i> Oh, yeah</i> ♪

10:51.543 --> 10:54.319
♪<i> I was at that</i>
<i> super killer party, too</i>
♪

10:54.470 --> 10:56.379
You weren't even in the show.

10:56.398 --> 10:57.805
♪<i> Yeah, but I was cool</i> ♪

10:57.899 --> 10:59.157
(grunts)

10:59.234 --> 11:00.659
♪<i> Lenny fell off the roof</i> ♪

11:00.886 --> 11:02.902
-What?
-♪
<i> Marge's parents got sued</i>
♪

11:02.996 --> 11:05.997
♪<i> And had to file</i>
<i> for bankruptcy</i>
♪

11:06.074 --> 11:08.241
Is that why I couldn't
go away to college?

11:08.393 --> 11:09.909
♪<i> Remember the time</i> ♪

11:10.061 --> 11:12.745
♪<i> When Jackie died</i> ♪

11:12.839 --> 11:14.172
Wait, I thought Jackie moved.

11:14.399 --> 11:16.841
-♪<i> No one saw the signs</i> ♪
-(gasps)

11:16.993 --> 11:18.401
♪<i> Together we cried</i> ♪

11:18.494 --> 11:21.179
♪<i> And then we made it</i>
<i> about ourselves</i>
♪

11:21.330 --> 11:23.239
♪<i> When the reporter came</i> ♪

11:23.332 --> 11:25.499
-What?!
-♪
<i> He worked for</i>
The Times ♪

11:25.593 --> 11:26.518
Which one?

11:26.669 --> 11:28.928
♪ The New York Times ♪

11:29.022 --> 11:31.097
♪<i> Such timey times</i> ♪

11:31.249 --> 11:32.857
How'd I miss all of this?

11:33.026 --> 11:36.736
♪<i> We were all together.</i> ♪

11:36.863 --> 11:38.446
Except me.

11:42.185 --> 11:44.035
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> Script notes and sound cues</i>
♪

11:44.187 --> 11:47.780
♪<i> They never saw me</i>
<i> as a friend</i>
♪

11:47.933 --> 11:50.858
♪<i> In my blacks in the backs</i>
<i> of the wings</i>
♪

11:50.877 --> 11:54.045
♪<i> I was unseen</i> ♪

11:55.941 --> 11:58.717
♪<i> So much for the magic</i> ♪

11:58.793 --> 12:04.013
♪<i> No one wants old Marjorie.</i> ♪

12:06.542 --> 12:07.967
(sobbing)

12:08.061 --> 12:11.712
(regular voice):
I was unpopular and never knew!

12:11.732 --> 12:13.714
All my best memories are ruined.

12:13.808 --> 12:16.642
I wish I had never done
this stupid musical again.

12:16.795 --> 12:20.572
As soon as Sasha showed up,
it was like I didn't exist.

12:20.799 --> 12:22.632
I never liked that Sasha Reed.

12:22.725 --> 12:25.134
Taking pop out of the fridge
without asking...

12:25.153 --> 12:26.578
getting us sued...

12:27.897 --> 12:29.655
Of course!
It's all Sasha's fault.

12:29.808 --> 12:32.976
Someone ought to teach
that Broadway big shot a lesson.

12:32.994 --> 12:35.903
Mom, do you
still have a computer?

12:35.997 --> 12:39.406
(dial-up modem whining)

12:39.501 --> 12:43.319
Last night I made some
very interesting discoveries,

12:43.412 --> 12:46.747
requiring the printing
of a revised playbill.

12:46.841 --> 12:48.266
(clears throat)

12:48.584 --> 12:51.677
(Disney princess voice):
♪
<i> I'll refer you to page three</i>
♪

12:51.830 --> 12:54.347
♪<i> To an updated biography</i> ♪

12:54.499 --> 12:56.332
♪<i> Of which you must see</i> ♪

12:56.351 --> 12:59.018
♪<i> Certain to change your view</i> ♪

12:59.112 --> 13:03.531
♪<i> Of the beloved ingenue</i> ♪

13:04.600 --> 13:06.025
♪<i> Sasha! Poof</i> ♪

13:06.102 --> 13:07.268
♪<i> The truth</i> ♪

13:08.437 --> 13:12.106
♪<i> She's never been in</i>
<i> a Broadway musical or play?</i>
♪

13:12.125 --> 13:16.443
♪<i> She was never in</i> Pippin,
Show Boat,
<i> or</i>
Cabaret? ♪

13:16.538 --> 13:20.023
♪<i> She didn't sign autographs</i>
<i> at a stage door-a?</i>
♪

13:20.116 --> 13:24.636
♪<i> She worked at</i>
<i> the Herald Square Sephora?</i>
♪

13:24.863 --> 13:27.196
♪<i> Lost hope, gave up</i>
<i> and moved the day</i>
♪

13:27.290 --> 13:30.700
♪<i> She didn't get a callback</i>
<i> for</i>
Hairspray ♪

13:30.793 --> 13:33.144
♪<i> She's a fraudway baby</i> ♪

13:33.371 --> 13:34.795
♪<i> A phony, a fake</i> ♪

13:34.964 --> 13:38.632
♪<i> She ain't got what it takes</i> ♪

13:38.726 --> 13:40.652
♪<i> She's a fraudway baby</i> ♪

13:40.879 --> 13:42.970
♪<i> She doesn't know</i>
<i> Sutton Foster</i>
♪

13:43.064 --> 13:44.730
♪<i> This broad's an imposter</i> ♪

13:44.883 --> 13:47.850
♪<i> She's had you wrapped</i>
<i> around her finger</i>
♪

13:47.902 --> 13:49.494
♪<i> For days</i> ♪

13:49.645 --> 13:52.221
♪<i> But she's nothing</i>
<i> but a hair-extentioned</i>
♪

13:52.240 --> 13:53.998
♪<i> Makeup-slinging,</i>
<i> Botox-forehead</i>
♪

13:54.225 --> 13:55.149
♪<i> Lying, cheating</i> ♪

13:55.168 --> 14:00.004
♪<i> Baby fraudway...</i> ♪

14:01.566 --> 14:03.383
♪ ♪

14:04.827 --> 14:06.327
So you don't know the people

14:06.421 --> 14:09.013
you said you knew
but who are they?

14:09.240 --> 14:10.849
Marge Bouvier, you're...

14:11.017 --> 14:12.183
mean!

14:12.410 --> 14:14.352
(sobbing)

14:15.689 --> 14:19.265
Well, I'm sure you're all
as angry at Sasha as I am,

14:19.359 --> 14:21.601
but now we can wipe
the slate clean

14:21.695 --> 14:24.845
and really come together
as a theater family.

14:24.939 --> 14:27.181
Without Sasha, there's no show.

14:27.275 --> 14:30.943
You ruined everything,
you... techie!

14:31.096 --> 14:33.187
But, w-w-wait.
She made it all up.

14:33.206 --> 14:34.706
She's a liar!

14:34.933 --> 14:36.766
I think this is
the kind of thing

14:36.859 --> 14:40.603
that makes people not want
to invite you to stuff.

14:40.696 --> 14:42.046
(growls)

14:47.629 --> 14:49.888
Stupid, ungrateful cast.

14:50.115 --> 14:51.948
Did you sleep at all last night?

14:52.041 --> 14:54.041
"We don't care
that Sasha's a liar."

14:54.135 --> 14:55.709
"We still love her
more than you."

14:55.803 --> 14:58.229
Mo-om!
Bart replaced my Kashi cereal

14:58.381 --> 15:00.881
with woodchips
from the hamster cage!

15:00.975 --> 15:03.217
So? You didn't notice
till I told you.

15:03.236 --> 15:04.794
-(growls)
-(yelps)

15:04.812 --> 15:07.054
-What's wrong with Mom?
-Well, kids, your mother has

15:07.132 --> 15:10.057
severely pissed off
all the theater weirdos--

15:10.135 --> 15:11.225
of which I am now one--

15:11.244 --> 15:13.653
but she can't see
it's her fault.

15:13.805 --> 15:15.562
So... are you gonna tell her?

15:15.657 --> 15:20.251
Indeed I am, and there's
only one way to do it.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.586
♪ ♪

15:23.256 --> 15:25.239
♪<i> When your partner's</i>
<i> in a tizzy</i>
♪

15:25.333 --> 15:27.483
♪<i> Flossing till she's dizzy</i> ♪

15:27.502 --> 15:30.336
♪<i> Clearly in the wrong,</i>
<i> but certain she's right</i>
♪

15:30.430 --> 15:32.764
♪<i> It's your responsibility</i> ♪

15:32.933 --> 15:34.657
♪<i> To imply her culpability</i> ♪

15:34.750 --> 15:37.936
♪<i> In a way that doesn't</i>
<i> instigate a fight</i>
♪

15:38.163 --> 15:41.105
-(grumbles)
-Whoops.

15:41.257 --> 15:43.608
♪<i> Don't escalate the situation</i> ♪

15:43.777 --> 15:45.276
♪<i> Or add further complication</i> ♪

15:45.503 --> 15:48.404
♪<i> Mince your words,</i>
<i> so as never to encroach</i>
♪

15:49.598 --> 15:51.174
♪<i> Deliver your advice</i> ♪

15:51.192 --> 15:52.675
♪<i> But make sure to do it nice</i> ♪

15:52.694 --> 15:56.037
♪<i> For it's best to use</i>
<i> a delicate approach</i>
♪

15:56.957 --> 15:58.814
Marge, darling...

15:58.816 --> 16:00.274
Leave me alone!

16:00.368 --> 16:02.609
Marge, listen!
I'm being delicate!

16:02.704 --> 16:04.278
Oh, are you?

16:05.465 --> 16:07.948
♪<i> Now, I know you may think</i>
<i>you were just in your actions</i>
♪

16:07.968 --> 16:09.859
♪<i> But it makes my heart sink</i>
<i> to see your infractions</i>
♪

16:09.952 --> 16:11.877
♪<i> Your feelings were hurt,</i>
<i> but it's malice you blurt</i>
♪

16:11.972 --> 16:14.472
♪<i> Your transaction</i>
<i> compels a retraction</i>
♪

16:16.884 --> 16:18.476
Oh, you're right, Homie.

16:18.703 --> 16:20.203
It's all my fault.

16:20.296 --> 16:23.206
I did the one thing
a stage manager must never do:

16:23.299 --> 16:26.317
I put myself before the show.

16:27.511 --> 16:28.377
You see, kids?

16:28.546 --> 16:31.214
♪<i> It's best to use a delicate</i> ♪

16:31.232 --> 16:32.565
♪<i> Approach.</i> ♪

16:32.659 --> 16:33.899
(toilet flushes)

16:34.052 --> 16:35.735
I have to make things right.

16:35.829 --> 16:37.069
You need to let me see

16:37.163 --> 16:40.223
the cast-only text chain.

16:40.391 --> 16:41.407
Yeah, I don't know.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.909
It's really not cool
for me to share it.

16:44.062 --> 16:46.412
Plus, you wouldn't get
any of the jokes.

16:46.564 --> 16:48.247
You might want
to skip over the stuff

16:48.399 --> 16:49.507
with your name in it.

16:49.658 --> 16:50.900
Sasha hasn't left town.

16:50.993 --> 16:52.552
There's still time.

16:53.905 --> 16:55.087
(sniffles)

16:55.240 --> 16:57.015
Why would Marge do that to me?

16:57.166 --> 16:58.999
I was never mean to her.

16:59.093 --> 17:00.593
I never even talked to her!

17:00.687 --> 17:03.521
Yeah, we don't care
that you only sell makeup

17:03.748 --> 17:06.173
and that you're a huge liar.

17:06.192 --> 17:08.434
I miss high school.

17:08.586 --> 17:11.029
Remember the night
of the cast party?

17:11.180 --> 17:14.348
You and me... in the hot tub?

17:14.367 --> 17:16.759
That night really happened?

17:16.778 --> 17:18.036
I thought I imagined it.

17:18.187 --> 17:19.612
It was real.

17:19.764 --> 17:22.189
And I've never had better.

17:22.208 --> 17:23.783
(grunts)
Ah...

17:23.877 --> 17:26.452
Sasha!
Sasha, I'm so sorry.

17:26.546 --> 17:28.379
Once my husband
sang and danced to me

17:28.531 --> 17:30.940
about what I did,
I felt terrible.

17:31.033 --> 17:33.718
I acted like
such a crazy teenager.

17:33.887 --> 17:36.295
All I wanted to do was
recapture my glory days,

17:36.447 --> 17:38.705
when I could've
become anything...

17:38.874 --> 17:40.283
instead of what I really am,

17:40.376 --> 17:42.709
a floor manager at Sephora.

17:42.878 --> 17:43.953
(sighs)

17:43.971 --> 17:45.063
Sales associate.

17:45.290 --> 17:48.149
I guess we both wanted
to be stars again.

17:48.976 --> 17:49.975
There she is.

17:50.052 --> 17:51.051
Probably called us here

17:51.071 --> 17:52.962
to expose the lies
the rest of us put

17:52.964 --> 17:54.463
in our playbill bios.

17:54.632 --> 17:55.815
What lies?

17:55.967 --> 17:58.058
I am
"thrilled to reprise my role

17:58.152 --> 18:00.411
as Steve/Ensemble."

18:00.563 --> 18:02.822
I was supposed
to manage the stage,

18:02.916 --> 18:06.066
but instead I just managed
to screw everything up.

18:06.235 --> 18:07.919
But there's still time
to put on the best show

18:08.088 --> 18:10.070
of the latter part
of our lives.

18:10.164 --> 18:12.590
What do you say?
Should we give it a try?

18:12.741 --> 18:14.032
Oh, why should we?

18:14.094 --> 18:17.320
What has trying
ever gotten anyone?

18:17.338 --> 18:19.347
♪ ♪

18:20.825 --> 18:22.491
♪<i> I could've been a crooner</i> ♪

18:22.585 --> 18:24.602
♪<i> Star of stage and screen</i> ♪

18:24.829 --> 18:26.178
♪<i> But I'd just as sooner</i> ♪

18:26.331 --> 18:29.774
♪<i> Drink away my dream</i> ♪

18:30.001 --> 18:32.001
-♪<i> Never try.</i> ♪
-SASHA: Stop!

18:32.094 --> 18:34.170
That's the saddest thing
I've ever heard.

18:34.263 --> 18:38.432
Barney, nobody needs
to do this show more than you.

18:38.526 --> 18:42.011
♪<i> Except me!</i> ♪

18:42.104 --> 18:43.437
-(cheering)
-Yay!

18:43.456 --> 18:44.847
♪ ♪

18:44.866 --> 18:46.866
It's a full house, so...

18:46.960 --> 18:49.702
♪<i> Places, everybody.</i> ♪

18:49.871 --> 18:52.779
Marge, when I'm onstage
and it's not my turn to talk,

18:52.799 --> 18:55.258
-can I look at my phone?
-No.

18:57.362 --> 19:00.221
♪ ♪

19:12.134 --> 19:13.559
It's almost midnight.

19:13.711 --> 19:15.194
What's going to happen?

19:18.992 --> 19:19.973
Oops.

19:19.993 --> 19:21.475
Five, four...

19:21.494 --> 19:24.370
Three, two, one!

19:26.166 --> 19:28.315
-(cheering)
-So the show just ends?

19:28.334 --> 19:29.725
What a cop-out!

19:29.744 --> 19:31.560
At least at the end
of
<i> Rent</i>
you get to see

19:31.562 --> 19:33.004
Mimi come back to life.

19:33.155 --> 19:34.914
This is just lazy.

19:35.066 --> 19:38.050
-♪ ♪
-(cheering)

19:40.254 --> 19:43.088
Marge, thanks for reminding me
how good it feels

19:43.183 --> 19:45.408
to be a big fish
in a small pond.

19:45.576 --> 19:47.593
I guess that's why
you never left.

19:47.745 --> 19:49.503
Actually, I think
it was because my parents

19:49.597 --> 19:52.523
couldn't afford college
after a lawsuit from a party

19:52.750 --> 19:55.175
you threw at my house
but didn't invite me to.

19:55.195 --> 19:58.029
Such timey times.

19:59.699 --> 20:01.941
(sighs)

20:02.035 --> 20:04.184
Oh, my God, it's really her.

20:04.204 --> 20:05.778
It's Marge Bouvier.

20:05.930 --> 20:08.372
Just ask her.

20:09.617 --> 20:11.667
Um, would you please
sign my prompt bible?

20:13.104 --> 20:14.045
You know me?

20:14.196 --> 20:16.464
You're a stage-managing icon!

20:19.219 --> 20:20.918
Would you go
to the diner with us?

20:21.070 --> 20:23.036
We'd die to hear
some of your stories.

20:23.130 --> 20:25.297
Invited to the diner.

20:25.391 --> 20:27.541
I'm getting cheese fries!

